The paper deals with signal recovery in compressed sensing, which is a topic that falls under multiple sub-categories in arXiv CS. However, the focus on the performance analysis of the $\ell_1$-synthesis approach with coherent frames suggests that the paper is most likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Signal Processing (cs.SP) sub-categories. The use of optimization techniques and the emphasis on the decaying property of the dual frame also suggest that the paper may be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the establishment of error bounds and the consideration of suitable conditions on the sensing matrix suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-category.
